 - 1.0.0
    -> Ability to append records to a file
    -> Move out EVT file operations to evt.c for a greater modularity
        - Rewrite evt2csv and csv2evt

 - Complete the Doxygen documentation.
    -> http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/autolink.html
    -> http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/commands.html

 - assert() function inputs etc.
    -> Don't assert errors, just what should never happen.
 - A program should be able to work without processing exceptions

 - evtdump or something like that
    -> A switch for showing just basic info

    -> Ability to dump event log records from any stream
        - The problem with wrapped records can be solved by checking
          the record data and eventually searching for the record length
          from the position of the header
        - This solution however requires that the log file
          is continuous and not fragmented or damaged
    -> Statistics - total number of records, frequency of various
       event sources and IDs, ...

    -> Event ID 6161 - Source: Print - A file failed to print: the name
       of the file that failed, username, printer
    -> Event ID 35 - Source: W32Time - System uses NTP to sync time:
       provides the IP address assigned to the interface
    -> Event ID 1007 - Source: WinDefend - malware detected, event strings
       contain information about the malware

